Phyllodes with non-anastomosing veins or veins obscure

Phyllodes 6–25 wide, lateral veins prominent; peduncles scurfy with resin cells and sometimes hairs

Phyllodes alternate

Branchlets not viscid

Phyllodes and branches not roughened

Phyllodes alternate

Branchlets and phyllodes not viscid

Branchlets and phyllodes not viscid

Midrib close to one margin

Phyllodes more than 2 cm long

Peduncles glabrous

Branchlets terete or ridged but ridges not viscid

Phyllodes more than 5 mm wide (rarely some to 3 mm wide)

Heads with fewer than 40 flowers

Gland 0–3 mm above pulvinus; pulvinus 1–6 mm long
